1. ARCHITECTURE OVERVIEW
Alkahest is a self-contained portable wireless audit platform. Every component has a defined role:
ESP32 WROOM (Marauder) — the wireless tool. Does the active work: beacon spam, deauth, probe sniffing, PMKID capture, Bluetooth scanning.
Raspberry Pi Zero W — the brain and relay. Manages serial comms to ESP32, runs Python scripts, hosts the SSH access point.
Anker Battery — powers both devices independently via USB.
Tablet/Phone — your terminal window. SSH into Pi over Alkahest hotspot.
Full control chain:
Tablet -> SSH -> Alkahest hotspot (Pi Zero W) -> USB serial -> Marauder (ESP32)
Why the Pi Zero W is relay-only
The Pi Zero W (2017, original model) is single-core ARMv6 with 512MB RAM. Kismet will choke it. This is not a limitation — it is a role definition. The Zero W manages comms, runs lightweight Python, and hosts the hotspot. The ESP32 does the capture work.
Note: Do not confuse this with the Pi Zero 2W (quad-core). This build uses the original single-core Zero W.
