4. ALKAHEST HOTSPOT CONFIGURATION
The Pi Zero W broadcasts its own Wi-Fi network called Alkahest. Your tablet connects to this network and SSHes in. No external internet required — fully self-contained.
The NetworkManager problem
Raspberry Pi OS uses NetworkManager to manage Wi-Fi. By default it will connect wlan0 to any saved home network , overriding hostapd before it can start.
WARNING: Deleting the home network connection will immediately drop SSH access if you are connected via that network. Always have a keyboard/monitor fallback or ensure hostapd will come up before cutting the home connection.
Files configured
/etc/dhcpcd.conf (appended)
interface wlan0
    static ip_address=192.168.4.1/24
    nohook wpa_supplicant
/etc/hostapd/hostapd.conf (created)
interface=wlan0
driver=nl80211
ssid=test
hw_mode=g
channel=7
wpa=2
wpa_passphrase=password blank 
wpa_key_mgmt=WPA-PSK
/etc/default/hostapd (created)
DAEMON_CONF="/etc/hostapd/hostapd.conf"
/etc/dnsmasq.conf (created)
interface=wlan0
dhcp-range=192.168.4.2,192.168.4.20,255.255.255.0,24h
/etc/rc.local (created — boot persistence)
#!/bin/bash
ip addr add 192.168.4.1/24 dev wlan0
exit 0
Why rc.local exists: dhcpcd.conf alone was not assigning the static IP because NetworkManager was claiming wlan0 first. rc.local forces the IP assignment at boot after all services are up.
